Subathons, inherently are about numbers. There’s a goal, and everyone is excited to help reach it. If we were to meet or exceed any goals set, my brain would tell me I haven’t deserved it. If we reached no goal, my brain would count that as confirmation that my content sucks(3/5)

I honestly have been feeling like not only do I not deserve my platform but that I’m in a constant state of letting people down. I get that this is imposter syndrome at it’s finest, but I honestly don’t want to give any fuel to this fire. (2/5)

I am still very much an 18+ stream and am still using marijuana to cope with my intense chronic pain, and still feel comfortable sharing that with y'all, but I did also want to keep y'all in the loop on the changes that have been going on.
This is something that is very important to me and I think should be for all people who partake in marijuana, whether medicinally or not.

The exception mention above will be April 20th as I already have a planned charity stream to work with the Last Prisoner Project. This projects mission is to free incarcerated individuals that were incarcerated on marijuana charges.

I decided to stop smoking on stream (with an exception we'll talk about in a bit) because I want to foster a safe and inclusive and cozy space for everyone, not just a select few. I'm sorry if this changes things for the negative, I just wanted to be open and honest with y'all.
